<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-031-309 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 434 285</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Oct 21 1991 v8 n42 p29(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Tecmar adapter displays live TV on a PC screen. (Vision/1 TVAdapter) (brief article) (Product Announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sullivan, Kristina B.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Tecmar Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Tecmar Vision/1 (Graphics board) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionMicroprocessorsTelevision equipmentMultimedia technologyGraphics boards/cards.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Kristina B. SullivanandM;Among the new multimedia products unveiled at Comdex this week will be theVision/1 TV Adapter, a device that allows IBM PS/1 users to view livetelevision on their computer screens.andM;Developed by Tecmar of Solon, Ohio, the Vision/1 TV Adapter will displaybroadcast or cable television on a VGA computer monitor, said Tecmarofficials.andP;  The device will include a TV tuner and support video input from aVCR, laser-disk player or video camera, they said.andP;  An antenna or cable TVservice is needed to receive live television.andM;Vision/1 will also allow users to view full-motion video on the full screenor in a window.andP;  Users will be able to execute a software program, forexample, while viewing a news broadcast.andM;Channels, volume, color, tint, brightness, contrast and window location canbe controlled through a software menu included with the system, according tocompany officials.andM;Priced at $395, the external, 8-pound device attaches to the keyboard andmonitor of a PS/1.andP;  Video-input devices are then attached to connectors onthe back of Vision/1.andP;  The product is scheduled to become available Jan.andP;  15through PS/1 dealers.andM;Tecmar manufactures IBM Audio/Visual Multimedia adapter cards.andP;  Vision/1 isthe firm's first retail product intended for multimedia applications.andM;Tecmar can be reached at (216) 349-0600.andO;</TEXT></DOC>